Bank of Nova Scotia Invests $2.30 Million in Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:BUFF)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 

Bank of Nova Scotia bought a new stake in shares of Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:BUFF) during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The firm bought 100,000 shares of the company’s stock, valued at approximately $2,300,000. Bank of Nova Scotia owned approximately 0.05% of Blue Buffalo Pet Products at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Other large investors have also recently modified their holdings of the company. FNY Partners Fund LP boosted its position in Blue Buffalo Pet Products by 63.7% in the first quarter. FNY Partners Fund LP now owns 4,500 shares of the company’s stock valued at $103,000 after buying an additional 1,751 shares in the last quarter. Envestnet Asset Management Inc. boosted its position in Blue Buffalo Pet Products by 54.4% in the fourth quarter. Envestnet Asset Management Inc. now owns 5,019 shares of the company’s stock valued at $121,000 after buying an additional 1,769 shares in the last quarter. Russell Investments Group Ltd. bought a new position in Blue Buffalo Pet Products during the fourth quarter valued at $134,000. US Bancorp DE boosted its position in Blue Buffalo Pet Products by 38.5% in the first quarter. US Bancorp DE now owns 7,193 shares of the company’s stock valued at $165,000 after buying an additional 2,000 shares in the last quarter. Finally, Quantbot Technologies LP bought a new position in Blue Buffalo Pet Products during the first quarter valued at $191,000. Institutional investors and hedge funds own 88.38% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Blue Buffalo Pet Products Inc. alerts:



Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. (BUFF) opened at 23.19 on Friday. The firm has a market cap of $4.56 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 34.10 and a beta of 1.97. Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. has a one year low of $21.60 and a one year high of $27.50. The stock’s 50 day moving average is $23.21 and its 200-day moving average is $23.97. 




Blue Buffalo Pet Products (NASDAQ:BUFF) last posted its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 9th. The company reported $0.23 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.22 by $0.01. Blue Buffalo Pet Products had a net margin of 11.69% and a return on equity of 122.62%. The business had revenue of $302 million for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $300.27 million. During the same quarter in the previous year, the business posted $0.19 earnings per share. The business’s revenue was up 7.9% compared to the same quarter last year. On average, equities research analysts expect that Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. will post $0.92 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: This piece was posted by BNB Daily and is owned by of BNB Daily. If you are reading this piece on another website, it was stolen and republished in violation of United States & international copyright legislation. The legal version of this piece can be accessed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/21/bank-of-nova-scotia-acquires-new-position-in-blue-buffalo-pet-products-inc-nasdaqbuff-updated-updated.html. 
BUFF has been the topic of several recent research reports. Zacks Investment Research cut shares of Blue Buffalo Pet Products from a “hold” rating to a “strong sell” rating in a report on Tuesday, July 11th. Susquehanna Bancshares Inc reissued a “positive” rating on shares of Blue Buffalo Pet Products in a research note on Thursday, April 20th. J P Morgan Chase & Co reissued an “overweight” rating and issued a $25.00 price objective (down from $28.00) on shares of Blue Buffalo Pet Products in a research note on Wednesday, June 28th. Citigroup Inc. raised shares of Blue Buffalo Pet Products from a “buy” rating to a “top pick” rating in a research note on Tuesday, April 18th. Finally, Off Wall Street assumed coverage on shares of Blue Buffalo Pet Products in a research note on Wednesday, June 21st. They issued a “sell” rating on the stock. Three investment analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, two have assigned a hold rating, six have issued a buy rating and one has assigned a strong buy rating to the company. Blue Buffalo Pet Products presently has a consensus rating of “Hold” and an average price target of $28.40.
About Blue Buffalo Pet Products
Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc (BBPP) is a holding company. The Company operates as a pet food company. The Company, through its subsidiaries, develops, produces, markets and sells pet food under product lines, including BLUE Life Protection Formula, BLUE Wilderness, BLUE Basics, BLUE Freedom and BLUE Natural Veterinary Diet lines. 

 
